Investing decisions driven by
emotions can sabotage even the most rationally constructed
portfolio, according to academic studies and research data. To
see the financial toll of not investing at a consistent pace,
 click here .  The interactive graphic tracks 20 years of erratic buying
and selling by investors based on data from research firm
Dalbar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
